{
  "texts": [
    "The document weight is the sum of the weights of the query term.",
    "Ponte et al. [53] proposed a language model that considers a passage of natural language text as a discrete time series.",
    "They utilized probabilistic models to estimate the probability of a document being relevant based directly on a particular probability distribution and a language model to predict the probability of a given sequence of words occurring in a sentence.",
    "Neural Ranking ModelsTraditional retrieval models obtain ranking scores by searching for exact matches of words in both the query and the document.",
    "However, this limits the availability of positional and semantic information and may lead to 𝑣𝑜𝑐𝑎𝑏𝑢𝑙𝑎𝑟𝑦 𝑚𝑖𝑠𝑚𝑎𝑡𝑐ℎ [126]."
